[{"id":"VR781567","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div>Which of the following correctly represents the total energy of the block-spring system when the block reaches position <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x equals 2 x sub 0\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"x equals 2 x sub 0\" overflow=\"scroll\"> <mi>x</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mn>2</mn> <msub> <mi>x</mi> <mn>0</mn> </msub> </math></span></span>?</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n","rubricRef":"VR781567_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A block of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"m\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>m</mi></math></span></span> is attached to one end of a spring with the other end of the spring attached to a wall. The block slides with negligible friction on a horizontal surface, as shown. When the block is at position <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x equals x sub 0\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"x equals x sub 0\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>x</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span>, the block has speed <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"v equals v sub 0\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"v equals v sub 0\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span> and the total energy of the block-spring system is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"E sub 0\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"E sub 0\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span>. When the block reaches position <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x equals 2 x sub 0\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"x equals 2 x sub 0\" overflow=\"scroll\"> <mi>x</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mn>2</mn> <msub> <mi>x</mi> <mn>0</mn> </msub> </math></span></span>, the block momentarily comes to rest.</p>\n\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a spring that is attached to a wall on its left end and is attached to a block of mass m on its right end. The block is on a horizontal surface and is moving to the right with speed v equals v sub 0. Points x equals 0, x equals x sub 0, and x equals 2 times x sub 0 are evenly spaced on the horizontal surface. At the moment shown, the block is at the point x equals x sub 0. The point x equals 0 is labeled “Equilibrium.”\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR781567.g01.svg\" /></div>\n"}],"choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"0\"><math alttext=\"0\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>0</mn></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"E sub 0\"><math alttext=\"E sub 0\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 times E sub 0\"><math alttext=\"2 times E sub 0\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"4 times E sub 0\"><math alttext=\"4 times E sub 0\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>4</mn><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":1}]